          "reviewBody": "Areas for Improvement:\n\n1. The teaching pace is initially slow, resulting in only 50% of textbook chapters being covered by December.\n\n2. Despite the high fees, entire textbooks are often not completed within the academic year.\n\n3. Worksheets are typically distributed only during exams or just prior to exams, which can be inadequate preparation for students.\n\n4. \"\"\"Unfortunately, since joining SGVP School, we have noticed that our child has started learning inappropriate language and behaviors, which we attribute to the school environment.\"\n\n5. \"\"\"The school management seems to prioritize profit over education, as evident from the substantial fee hike last year. The increase was approximately ₹30,000, broken down into:\n- ₹15,000 as term fee\n- ₹10,000 as school fee\n- ₹5,000-₹6,000 as bus fee\n\nThank you.",
